            <arrangement id="aspace_08b58eb1afd975e444c6509adf5429ff">
               <head>Arrangement</head>
               <p>Sound recordings are arranged according to a numbering system assigned by MacLise, "GM/AM 001-025." "GM" stands for Gerard Malanga, who assisted Hetty MacLise in rehousing the tapes before their transfer to the Beinecke Library. "AM" stands for Angus MacLise.</p>
            </arrangement>
            <scopecontent id="aspace_18167fcc03b34b3e4b773883e577241a">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>The sound recordings consist of 28 reel-to-reel audio tapes. Most tapes have been rehoused into new reel boxes by Hetty MacLise and Malanga. Original boxes are filed next to the rehoused tapes since the original boxes contain MacLise's notes. Titles have been transcribed from original boxes. Tapes 1-9, and 24 are 7.5 inch reels. Tapes 10-23 and 25 are 5 inch reels.</p>
               <p>There are three numbered tapes at the end of the series that are in original boxes. These tapes include GM/AM numbers that do not correspond to rehoused tapes. All are 7.5 inch reels. It is not clear as to why they were assigned duplicate numbers but were not rehoused. It is possible that they were not reviewed by Hetty MacLise and Malanga.</p>
            </scopecontent>
